---
const comparisons = [
  ["Docker/Kubernetes", "Great at scale, heavy when you just need a VPS release path."],
  ["PaaS platforms", "Fast to start, but pricing and platform rules become part of your architecture."],
  ["Manual SSH", "Transparent, but easy to forget a step under pressure."],
  ["ShipNode", "Keeps the server visible and turns repeatable release hygiene into commands."],
];
---

<section class="shell-section why" id="why-shipnode">
  <div class="shell-container why-grid">
    <div class="why-copy">
      <p class="section-kicker">Why it exists</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">No magic, just good server hygiene.</h2>
      <p class="section-copy">
        ShipNode is for developers who want a real server without rebuilding a deploy
        platform from shell history. It keeps the moving parts plain: SSH, rsync,
        releases, PM2, Caddy, health checks, and rollback.
      </p>

      <div class="comparison" aria-label="Deployment approach comparison">
        {comparisons.map(([name, copy]) => (
          <article>
            <h3>{name}</h3>
            <p>{copy}</p>
          </article>
        ))}
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="config-card" aria-label="shipnode.conf example">
      <div class="config-top">
        <span>shipnode.conf</span>
        <span>production</span>
      </div>
      <pre><code>APP_TYPE=backend
SSH_USER=deploy
SSH_HOST=203.0.113.10
SSH_PORT=22

REMOTE_PATH=/var/www/api
PM2_APP_NAME=api
BACKEND_PORT=3000
DOMAIN=api.example.com

ZERO_DOWNTIME=true
HEALTH_CHECK_PATH=/health
HEALTH_CHECK_RETRIES=3
KEEP_RELEASES=5</code></pre>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .why-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) minmax(360px, 0.72fr);
    gap: clamp(2rem, 6vw, 6rem);
    align-items: start;
  }

  .section-title {
    max-width: 780px;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .section-copy {
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .comparison {
    margin-top: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border-primary);
  }

  .comparison article {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(150px, 0.35fr) minmax(0, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
    padding: 1rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-primary);
  }

  h3 {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .comparison p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.94rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }

  .comparison article:last-child {
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--accent-muted), transparent 62%);
    margin-inline: -1rem 0;
    padding-inline: 1rem 0;
  }

  .comparison article:last-child h3 {
    color: var(--accent-hover);
  }

  .config-card {
    position: sticky;
    top: 6rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    background: var(--bg-code);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md), inset 0 1px 0 rgba(237, 237, 223, 0.08);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .config-top {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: 1rem;
    padding: 0.85rem 1rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-primary);
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.72rem;
  }

  .config-top span:first-child {
    color: var(--accent-hover);
  }

  pre {
    padding: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.4rem);
    overflow-x: auto;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    font-size: clamp(0.76rem, 1.35vw, 0.9rem);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  @media (max-width: 940px) {
    .why-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .config-card {
      position: static;
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 560px) {
    .comparison article {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 0.4rem;
    }

    .config-top {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
